-- Ipsen Names De Garidel as Chief Executive as Belingard Quits Over Strategy
-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 2010-10-11T16:51:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/ipsen-names-de-garidel-as-chief-executive-as-belingard-quits-over-strategy.html
Ipsen named Marc de Garidel chairman
and chief executive officer, replacing Jean-Luc Belingard who is
leaving the group over “strategic differences,” the company
said in an e-mailed statement today.  De Garidel, 52, will take over from Belingard on Nov. 22,
and aims to strengthen the group’s operations in the U.S. and
emerging markets, Ipsen said in the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  